## Background 
Functions act to condense code into simple, repeatable calls to lines of code which makes up the heart of R. 

All functions in R have 3 components:

1. A **name** to call functions 
2. One or more **arguments** that are fed into the function separated by commas 
3. The **body** of the function, lines of code that describe what the function does 

## First exploration with functions in R

Writing a function that adds 1 to arg x 


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
add <- function(x) {
  x + 1 
}

add(2)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] 3
```


:::
:::


Imputing a different object types


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
