## Third function
>Q. Write a function called `generate_protein()` that generates a user specified length proteins equeince in FASTA like format


::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
generate_protein <- function(n){
  aas <- c("A", "G", "V", "L", "I", "P", "F", "Y", "W", "S", "T", "C", "M", "D", "E", "K", "R", "H", "N", "Q")
  seq <- sample(aas, n, T)
  seq <- paste(seq, collapse = "")
  return(seq)
}
```
:::



::: {.cell}

```{.r .cell-code}
generate_protein(15)
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}

```
[1] "WFAKWYHIKYFVLIE"
```


:::
:::




